        <td style="width:268px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true">A </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Spline</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Sketch-Elements" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">sketch-element</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. It is defined by the position, gradient, curvature of constraint points along the Spline shape.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The Spline can be &apos;open&apos;</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> or &apos;closed&apos;</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">If you click a Spline one time, then &apos;handles&apos; show</text><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. You can drag the arrow-heads to control the gradient and the curvature of the spline at the Point.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">You can drag the &apos;handles&apos; in the Mechanism- and Part-Editors.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
